<div id="review_102439396" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/102439396" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2329228-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433629372p2/2329228.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/102439396?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/2329228-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451526885" href="/book/show/540665.Six_Characters_in_Search_of_an_Author">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=and-a-half">and-a-half</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=plays">plays</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer102439396" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6612675034725791873"><b>2.5 Stars</b><br/><br/>A part of my brain is growling that I should put on my big girl panties and acknowledge that this is a Very Clever Play probably full of Historical And Philosophical Importance and worth All The Stars. Or at least, more than two. <br/><br/>It is certainly a <i>clever</i> play within a play within a play. And when you layer in the 1921 date, why, it positively seems genius. <br/><br/>The philosophy is very postmodern, questioning and critiquing even while busting through the 4th wall and exploring art and identity</span>
  <span id="freeText6612675034725791873" style="display:none"><b>2.5 Stars</b><br /><br />A part of my brain is growling that I should put on my big girl panties and acknowledge that this is a Very Clever Play probably full of Historical And Philosophical Importance and worth All The Stars. Or at least, more than two. <br /><br />It is certainly a <i>clever</i> play within a play within a play. And when you layer in the 1921 date, why, it positively seems genius. <br /><br />The philosophy is very postmodern, questioning and critiquing even while busting through the 4th wall and exploring art and identity. <br /><br />But...it was all rather sordid. The actors and their swearing. The characters and their tangled web of semi-incest. Some aspects just didn't age well, like the villainous pimp's accent. Other vulgarities seem almost quaint when you consider modern media. <br /><br />It was clever, thought-provoking, but not my cup of tea. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6612675034725791873" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


