<div id="review_2899793663" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2899793663" />
    <a title="Mohamad Shibly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60212235-mohamad-shibly"><img alt="Mohamad Shibly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498045612p2/60212235.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2899793663?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mohamad Shibly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mohamad Shibly" href="/user/show/60212235-mohamad-shibly">Mohamad Shibly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2899793663" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1285988131675028950">I chose this book because I liked the title. This is one of those open ended plays, maybe belonging to the theater of the absurd. It is a play about a play, where the six characters who were created by some author who seemed to be dead, and the characters need another author to write their roles or lives, while acting their own parts to become the puppets of their own selves, eventually as the play goes we come to realize that the characters already were their own authors. Mask and actor, person</span>
  <span id="freeText1285988131675028950" style="display:none">I chose this book because I liked the title. This is one of those open ended plays, maybe belonging to the theater of the absurd. It is a play about a play, where the six characters who were created by some author who seemed to be dead, and the characters need another author to write their roles or lives, while acting their own parts to become the puppets of their own selves, eventually as the play goes we come to realize that the characters already were their own authors. Mask and actor, persona and person stand face to face in the play’s central mirror.<br />I loved most of all the idea behind the book which is open to so much interpretation, i also loved the Father character and his philosophical comments every now and then.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1285988131675028950" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


